    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-07-11</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-10-31T22:09:59Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Over-the-Counter Speculation Act - Amends the Commodity Exchange Act to authorize the Commodity Futures Trading Commission (CFTC), in the case of a major market disturbance, to require any trader required to report under this Act to take action to maintain or restore orderly trading in any contract listed for trading on a registered entity, including: (1) liquidation of any over-the-counter transaction; and (2) fixing of any limit that may apply to a market position involving any over-the-counter transaction acquired in good faith before the date of the CFTC's determination of a major market disturbance.</p><p>Defines &quot;major market disturbance&quot; and &quot;over-the-counter transaction.&quot;</p><p>Sets forth reporting and recordkeeping requirements.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
